name: Pig Stool by Dimitri Omersa in Brown Leather, 1950s

condition.details: Refinished. Wear consistent with age and use. Minor losses. As it is a hand-crafted item it has bent imperfections on the legs. Minor wear commensurate with age and use. The tail and one eye are missing. Photos are a part of the item's description.

specifications.rawSpecificationsHTML: Handsome handmade leather pig footstool / ottoman designed and manufactured at the 1950s by Dimitri Omersa for Liberty of London. Pig ottoman first made in the 1930's for Liberty 's London during decades and later from the 1960's-1980's for Abercrombie & Fitch. This charming vintage pig form footstool is made of leather with eye and ears details. The tail and one of the eyes is missing. It has feet with metal pads for added support and stability. The leather is in very good vintage condition and it has been carefully nourished. This foot stool will be a nice addition to any Scandinavian Modern, Midcentury, Contemporary or Classical ambiance. Perfect to be used as footstool or cool animal sculpture and interesting for windows dressings and shops. Overall Measures: 64 cm W x 25 cm D x 33 cm H // 25,19 in W x 9,84 in D x 12,99 in H
